 501:     """
 502: 	Given an alleletable file, this function will split the alleletable into independent
 503: 	lineage groups and estimate the indel formation probabilities. This is done by
 504: 	treating each intBC as an independent observation and counting how many intBC contain
 505: 	a specific mutation, irrespective of the cell.
 506: 
 507: 	:param at:
 508: 		The allele table pandas DataFrame
 509: 	:param group_var:
 510: 		Columns by which to group and count indels. This will effectively serve as the denominator when calculating the 
 511: 		frequenceis (i.e. N intBCs or M * N_m for M lineage groups and N_m intBCs per lineage groups if you group by intBC and LG)
 512: 	:return:
 513: 		An M x 2 pandas DataFrame mapping all M mutations to the frequency and raw counts
 514: 		of how many intBC this mutation appeared on.
